# Accessio Ops Module - VB.NET Forms Style Coding Rules

## PURPOSE
This document defines coding standards for the Accessio Ops module to maintain consistency with VB.NET Forms development patterns. All React components should be written in a style that feels natural to VB.NET developers.

## CODE STYLE RULES

### 1. Function Declarations (NOT Arrow Functions)
**REQUIRED:** Use explicit function declarations instead of arrow functions
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT (VB.NET style)
function handleButtonClick() {
  // Implementation
}

// ❌ WRONG (JavaScript shorthand)
const handleButtonClick = () => {
  // Implementation
};
```

### 2. Variable Declarations (Explicit and Descriptive)
**REQUIRED:** Use explicit variable declarations with descriptive names
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT (VB.NET style)
function handleTimerTick() {
  const currentSystemTime = new Date();
  const formattedTimeString = formatTime(currentSystemTime);
  setCurrentTime(formattedTimeString);
}

// ❌ WRONG (JavaScript shorthand)
const handleTimerTick = () => setCurrentTime(formatTime(new Date()));
```

### 3. Event Handler Naming (VB.NET Convention)
**REQUIRED:** Use VB.NET-style event handler names
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT (VB.NET style)
function handleTimerTick() { }        // Like Timer_Tick
function handleButtonClick() { }     // Like Button_Click
function handleFormLoad() { }         // Like Page_Load
function handleFormUnload() { }      // Like Page_Unload
function handleSelectedIndexChanged() { } // Like SelectedIndexChanged

// ❌ WRONG (JavaScript style)
const onTimerTick = () => { }
const onButtonClick = () => { }
```

### 4. Component Lifecycle (VB.NET Page Events)
**REQUIRED:** Use VB.NET-style comments and structure
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT (VB.NET style)
// Component mounted (like Page_Load event)
React.useEffect(() => {
  // Initialize component
  startTimer();
  subscribeToEvents();
  
  // Cleanup on unmount (like Page_Unload in VB.NET)
  return () => {
    stopTimer();
    unsubscribeFromEvents();
  };
}, []);

// ❌ WRONG (JavaScript style)
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setInterval(() => setCurrentTime(new Date()), 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(timer);
}, []);
```

### 5. State Management (VB.NET ViewState Style)
**REQUIRED:** Use explicit state declarations with VB.NET-style comments
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT (VB.NET style)
// Component state variables (like ViewState in VB.NET)
const [currentTime, setCurrentTime] = React.useState(new Date());
const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = React.useState(false);
const [errorMessage, setErrorMessage] = React.useState(null);

// ❌ WRONG (JavaScript style)
const [currentTime, setCurrentTime] = useState(new Date());
```

### 6. Comments (VB.NET Documentation Style)
**REQUIRED:** Include VB.NET analogies in all comments
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT (VB.NET style)
// Timer_Tick event handler (like Timer_Tick in VB.NET)
function handleTimerTick() {
  // Get current system time (like DateTime.Now in VB.NET)
  const currentSystemTime = new Date();
  
  // Update component state (like updating a Label control in VB.NET)
  setCurrentTime(currentSystemTime);
}

// ❌ WRONG (JavaScript style)
// Timer tick handler
const handleTimerTick = () => setCurrentTime(new Date());
```

### 7. Error Handling (VB.NET Try-Catch Style)
**REQUIRED:** Use explicit error handling with VB.NET-style comments
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT (VB.NET style)
function handleApiCall() {
  try {
    // API call logic (like calling a Web Service in VB.NET)
    const response = await fetch('/api/data');
    const data = await response.json();
    
    // Update UI (like binding data to controls in VB.NET)
    setData(data);
  } catch (error) {
    // Handle error (like Try-Catch in VB.NET)
    setErrorMessage(error.message);
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG (JavaScript style)
const handleApiCall = async () => {
  try {
    const response = await fetch('/api/data');
    setData(await response.json());
  } catch (error) {
    setErrorMessage(error.message);
  }
};
```

### 8. Component Structure (VB.NET Form Structure)
**REQUIRED:** Structure components like VB.NET forms
```javascript
// ✅ CORRECT (VB.NET style)
export default function ClusterConfigTab() {
  // 1. State variables (like form-level variables in VB.NET)
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = React.useState(false);
  
  // 2. Event handlers (like event subs in VB.NET)
  function handleButtonClick() { }
  function handleTimerTick() { }
  
  // 3. Component lifecycle (like Page_Load/Unload in VB.NET)
  React.useEffect(() => { }, []);
  
  // 4. Helper methods (like private methods in VB.NET)
  function formatDisplayValue() { }
  
  // 5. Render method (like form rendering in VB.NET)
  return (
    <div>
      {/* UI controls (like controls on a VB.NET form) */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

## ENFORCEMENT

All code changes in the Accessio Ops module must follow these rules. This ensures consistency for developers coming from VB.NET backgrounds and maintains readable, maintainable code.

